Package com.epoch.synthesis

Classes for holding and analyzing multistep syntheses.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DielsAlderStereo
    Sets the stereochemistry of the product of a Diels-Alder reaction.
    NamedCompound
    Name and imported molecule of a compound.
    RxnCondition
    Defines a reaction condition used by a Synthesis.
    SingleRxnSolver
    Calculates the products of a single reaction.
    SynthArrow
    Describes an arrow connecting two stages of a synthesis.
    SynthBadSMs
    Gets and stores compounds and substructures that students may try to use in synthesis responses but that cannot exist.
    Synthesis
    Wraps a response synthesis, and includes methods for analyzing its validity.
    SynthMenuOnlyRgts
    Gets and stores the SMILES definitions and names of reagents that students cannot draw, but must pull from the reagents menu that ACE provides.
    SynthParser
    Parses a synthesis into stages, stores the parsed synthesis.
    SynthSet
    Compares sets of molecules for mechanisms.
    SynthSolver
    Calculates the products of a stage and the indicated reaction conditions.
    SynthStage
    Contains data and references to items inside a rectangle (box, stage).
    SynthStarterRule
    Contains and uses an evaluator that determines whether a compound has a property that makes it a permissible starting material for a synthesis.
    SynthUtils
    Methods for coloring synthesis components.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    SynthError
    Contains the results of a failure of a synthesis operation.
